{"word":"μανθάνω","slug":"μανθάνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>μανϑάνω</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pres.\">pres.</a> tense derived from an <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ aor.\">aor.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἔμαθον\">ἔμαθον</a></el>] ‘acquire knowledge’, <b>learn<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> through instruction or receipt of information <b><a href='B:470 9:13'>Mt 9:13</a>; <a href='B:470 24:32'>24:32</a>; <a href='B:500 6:45'>J 6:45</a>; <a href='B:500 7:15'>7:15</a>; <a href='B:510 23:27'>Ac 23:27</a>; <a href='B:520 16:17'>Ro 16:17</a>; <a href='B:530 14:31'>1 Cor 14:31</a>, <a href='B:530 14:35'>35</a>; <a href='B:550 3:2'>Gal 3:2</a>; <a href='B:560 4:20'>Eph 4:20</a>; <a href='B:570 4:9'>Phil 4:9</a>; <a href='B:580 1:7'>Col 1:7</a>; <a href='B:610 2:11'>1 Ti 2:11</a>; <a href='B:620 3:7'>2 Ti 3:7</a>, <a href='B:620 3:14'>14</a>; <a href='B:730 14:3'>Rv 14:3</a></b> (but here the idea of ‘understand’ may be dominant)<b>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> through example or experience <b><a href='B:470 11:29'>Mt 11:29</a>; <a href='B:530 4:6'>1 Cor 4:6</a>; <a href='B:570 4:11'>Phil 4:11</a>; <a href='B:610 5:4'>1 Ti 5:4</a>, <a href='B:610 5:13'>13</a>; <a href='B:630 3:14'>Tit 3:14</a>; <a href='B:650 5:8'>Hb 5:8</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Μανασσῆς\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:μανία\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}